  <bioghist id="aspace_37fbe58dae4e890e78970b1c9410747d">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>The first winter short course (Dairy) was given in 1892-93. These courses were provided during the winter to teach practical education to non-traditional students. The courses were inline with Cornell's Land Grant mission. The majority of the students were New York State farmers.</p>  </bioghist>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_d5a14e95e873c13f74d2d176d9676568">
    <head>RELATED MATERIALS</head>
<p>See also New York State College of Agriculture Winter Short Course Scrapbooks, #21-34-4029.</p><p> See also the Michael L. and Catherine H. Whalen Collection of Cornelliana, #37-5-3784.</p><p> See also Dairy Industry Winter Course Student Record Cards, #21-19-1190.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
